  <summary date="2021-04-14T14:17:33Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Federal Adjustment of Income Rates Act or the FAIR Act

This bill modifies pay rates for federal employees in 2022. Specifically, the bill increases rates under the statutory pay systems and for prevailing rate employees by 2.2%, and increases locality pay by 1%.</summary>
